Ticket Update: Peterborough United
Posted:
Tue 03 May 2016
Latest News
Tickets for Blackpool's final game of the season at Peterborough United on Sunday remain on sale at the ticket office.
Tickets for the fixture, which kicks-off at 12.30pm, are priced as follows:
- 23 for Adults
- 14 for Seniors (60+)
- 14 for 18-21s
- 10 for Under-18s
Disabled supporters pay the relevant price class, with a carer ticket issued free of charge.
Tickets can be purchased from the Bloomfield Road ticket office until 3pm on Friday. Supporters are asked to note that a 3 price increase applies to tickets purchased on the day of the fixture.
